docs.snippet: A bizarre, almost comic, denouement marked a soccer game at Yankee Stadium last night, when 40 partisans of a "wronged" Italian team chased the 5-foot referee around the infield. The incident nearly touched off a riot.

docs.lead_paragraph: FAIRBANKS, Alaska-- In this Canadian centennial year of Expo 67, Alaska is trying hard to tell the world that it has just had 100 good years of its own. In 1867, the year in which the Dominion of Canada was formed, the United States paid $7.2-million for 586,400 square miles of land then known as Russian America.

headline.main: Alaska Has an Expo All Its Own
